  <a href="#1" id="1">
   TPA AND ANGIOPLASTIES
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Doctors from the University of Michigan Medical Center studied the effects of sending a few carefully selected heart patients home early.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   They found that these people had no unusual complications, got back to work sooner and had substantially lower medical bills.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Topol said the early discharges were made possible by two recent medical advances tissue plasminogen activator, or TPA, and angioplasty.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   The report represents the latest in a steady three-decade trend of sending heart attack patients home from the hospital after ever shorter stays.
  </a>
